pr_body:
testtools has too much magic, making it difficult to have direct access to test error information. Having access to that test error information is required to make the output from gabbi-run useful.

The change attempts to replicate the existing behavior of gabbi-run but add no more. That should be for later efforts.

@FND if you're able to confirm the "existing behavior" part then we can probably merge.

@rhyolight @scottpurdy please review
These are a couple unit tests to be included in the NuPIC build. They test the couple of NuPIC functions used by the [Numenta detector in NAB](https://github.com/numenta/NAB/blob/master/nab/detectors/numenta/numenta_detector.py); they don't extensively test the functions b/c there are specific NuPIC unit tests for that, e.g. [anomaly likelihood](https://github.com/numenta/nupic/blob/master/tests/unit/nupic/algorithms/anomaly_likelihood_test.py).

fixes #1912

…ll it first for source builds.

fixes #578 

@rhyolight - fyi

@oxtopus - please review, in particular the setup.py changes.

* Adding a new API in MXNet backend - `data_names, data_shapes = get_mxnet_model_info(model)` for users to be able to query MXNet backend to see what is underlying MXNet model metadata. 
* This API is typically useful for users using MXNetModelCheckpoint to save best model as native MXNet model but, through checkpoint they can't get the MXNet model details. So they will use this API for fetching those details to bind to MXNet module.

@kalyc @roywei

This patch accept string macros with hyphen and colon:

@string{pub-ieee-std = {IEEE}}
@string{pub-ieee-std:adr = {New York, NY, USA}}

and accept entry field names with period:

Dc.Date = {2004-01},
